                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">From the Bridgewater Methodist free Church</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-volume-rules" calendar="gregorian"
                        notAfter="1865-07-31T23:59:59+00:00" notBefore="1865-04-15T00:00:00+00:00"
                        >undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>This meeting desires to express its unfeigned regret that the triumphant course
                    of the late President Lincoln should have been cut short by the hand of an
                    assassin.</p>
                <p>This meeting also desire to express its deep sympathy for the American people in
                    this hour of trial and conflict. Nevertheless, they venture earnestly to desire
                    that, as truth is stronger than ever, the Almighty will be graciously pleased to
                    overrule all things for good, and to redound to his glory.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
